There are stickers, pins, and magnets which I‚Äôm selling through Redbubble - they‚Äôre available with several different LGBTQ  flag options, although I know I haven‚Äôt covered them all so if you notice your flag missing feel free to comment it below and I‚Äôll work on adding them in! And I‚Äôm selling shirts, sweaters, and hoodies through Teespring. 
          I mentioned that I‚Äôm saving money for my transition but that‚Äôs not the only thing the profits will go towards. My plan is for 80% of the profits to go towards saving for my transition, 10% towards funding the channel, and 10% to LGBTQ  charities. I‚Äôll leave a link to a google sheet below to show how your money is being divided for whatever product you may chose to get, as I want you all to have full transparency. I know the amount towards charities is low at the moment but I intend to increase that amount as I get closer to my goal for raising for my transition. I‚Äôm also going to be putting up a poll here each time there is a significant amount of money to donate and let you all choose from a few charities as well as suggest any you see fit! 
          I‚Äôm really excited about this! I was interested in ways I might be able to raise for my transition and bottom surgery through the channel, but I didn‚Äôt want to just ask people to donate as I‚Äôm aware of the influence that content creators can have and I don‚Äôt ever want that to be used to my advantage. I‚Äôm happy about this way as it allows me to give back to you all in the form of merch as well as to give back to the queer community as a whole by donating to charities and organizations. I hope that you enjoy this as well and if you have any questions or suggestions feel free to comment them below!

Teespring Merch Store: https://gremlinsunited.creator-spring.com/

        The Queer Resource is now a website! Feel free to check it out if you‚Äôre interested. It includes a section on queer terminology, queer history, LGBTQIA  organizations and small businesses you can support, transgender resources, LGBTQIA  artists, and more! Let me know if there‚Äôs any improvements I can make to the website moving forward!
